    "body": "Currently `num_workers` can wind up being `1` if a machine has only a single CPU (like a minimal cloud instance). In these cases, it might be worth warning users that they only have `1` worker and so they won't get the benefits of parallelism with Dask. Of course the messaging/communication may need a bit of thought to find the right balance.",
